A combined team of security personnel comprising men of the Nigeria Police Force, the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps, and the Department of State Security, have barricaded the Bauchi Assembly complex as some suspected thugs were said to have attempted to force their way into the complex’s gate to wreak havoc. The Nation had reported that a vote of no confidence was passed by 22 aggrieved members of the House last Friday on the Speaker, Abubakar Suleiman, and other principal officers. The unidentified thugs were said to have stormed the Complex entrance on Sunday at about 11 pm.   Niger orders suspension of mining activities in three…     Catholic Church denies abandoning victims of Owo terror…     Expectations high to see you deliver, Osinbajo tells new…   Confirming the development to the Nation on phone, the Special Adviser on State and National Assembly Liaison to Bauchi state Governor, Sani Mohammed Burra said, “Some unknown persons last night had attempted to gain entrance in the Hon. House Complex as a result of which the security persons have taken over the place to avoid breakdown of law and order”. “Immediately I was contacted, I informed the State Commissioner of Police on behalf of the State Government for necessary and prompt action. He too immediately mobilized personnel to the complex to ensure that no damage is done”. When contacted, the Spokesman of the Command, SP Ahmed Wakil did not pick up our Correspondent’s call nor reply to the message sent to him.